Whārangi 1: Haurongo
Henare, James Clendon Tau
1911–1989
Nō Ngā Puhi; he kaihautū, he kaiārahi hōia, he tangata ahu whenua, he poutoko iwi
I tuhia tēnei haurongo e Puna McConnell and Robin C. McConnell,, ā, i tāngia tuatahitia ki Ngā Tāngata Taumata Rau Ko te wāhanga , 2000.
I whānau a James Clendon (Hīmi Te Nana) Tau Hēnare ki Mōtatau, i te takiwā o Pēwhairangi (Bay of Islands), i te 18 o Noema o te tau 1911. Ko ia tētahi o ngā tamariki, tokowaru katoa rātou, a Hera Paerata rāua ko tana tāne, k
... (6974 chars skipped) ... 
e; pono ana ia kua kaha kē atu ia ki te whakahihiwa ake i ōna whakaaro, ki te kite ake i te kiko o te take, me te nuku kē atu o tōna pai ki te whakatepe i te mahi.
I tana kore e whakaae ki te tono mai a Te Puea Hērangi kia noho ia hei kaiārahi mō tōna iwi o Waikato, tuku rawa atu he pāmu māna, ko tana hokinga atu tēnā ki tana pāmu anō i Mōtatau. Hāunga te wā i a ia i Ākarana i ngā tau 1951 ki 1956 – ko ia nei te āpiha toko i te ora Māori mō te takiwā o te tāone nui o Ākarana, haere atu i Ākarana
... (6974 chars skipped) ...
a ki te whakahau, me tana noho heamana mai anō mō te rōpū reo Māori Wānanga Whakatauira, i tū ai te kōhanga reo.
Nō te 2 o Āperira o te tau 1989 i mate ai a Tā Hīmi Hēnare ki Kawakawa, ā, mahue ake ana ko tana hoa me ā rāua tamariki. I Ōtīria marae i Moerewa tōna tangihanga. Ko ētahi o ngā rangatira i tae atu ki te tangi ko te Kuini Māori, arā, ko te Arikinui, ko te Kāwana Tianara, ko te Pirimia me ngā hoa o Hīmi i te pakanga. Nehua ake ana a Tā Hīmi Hēnare i Mōtatau ki te nehu anō nei o te toa.

Kei roto i nga pepeke nga purapura kei te tuku i te koiora tino nui, he mea whakamiharo tonu nga tangata mai i te timatanga. Ko tenei tino ahuareka ko te take mo to tatou waahanga o nga pepa tae noa ki nga papanga.
Ngā pepa papanga
Nā te tini o a ratau waipiro, e pai ana te pata kia rite ki nga whaarangi tae mo nga tamariki iti me te rahi. Kia ngahau te tirotiro ki nga tauira kowhatu hei peera mo nga tamariki. Ka tuwhera i te hononga ki te tuwhera i te whārangi takitahi ki te whārangi whakaari o te papakupu:
Ka kitea e koe he maha o nga whaarangi tae koreutu me nga hoahoa hoahoa-tamariki ma nga tama me nga kotiro. Kei te taha o nga tauira mahi-a-ringa, nga panga-hoahoa a te tamaiti, nga tauira mo nga mahi arithmetic, nga whakaaro takaro me te tomokanga maatua ma nga maatua. Ko nga whaarangi karakara e tika ana ma nga tamariki mai i te kura tamariki ki te kura tuatahi. Na te tae i nga pikitia te whakatairanga i te ruruku-a-kanohi, te tino pukenga me te pukenga motuka, te auaha, te tuhi momo me te waatea i nga whakaaro o nga tamariki. Na te tini o a maatau kaupapa ka whakanui i te hihiri o ia tamaiti ki te hiahia ki te whai waa ki te karakara.
He paatai taau, he whakaaro, he whakahe, kua kitea ranei e koe he pepeha? Kei te ngaro koe i tetahi kaupapa me tuku ripoata, he pikitia karakara ranei hei hanga ma maatau? Korero mai ki a matou!

Pānuitia ngā kōrero a Te Horetā e whai ake nei, ka whiriwhiri ai i te kupu kei raro iho e ōrite ana te tikanga ki ia kupu kei ngā rārangi tuatahi. Me tō e koe te mea o te rārangi tuarua ki te mea e tika ana o te rārangi tuatahi. Hei te mutunga, pāwhiritia te pātene kia kitea mehemea kua eke panuku koe.
Ka noho rā mātou i Whitianga, ka puta taua kaipuke nei ki reira, ka kite atu ō mātou kaumātua i taua kaipuke, ka mea rātou he atua, ā, he tupua ngā tāngata o taua kaipuke, ā, ka tū te kaipuke, ā, ka hoe mai ngā poti ki uta, ka mea aua kaumātua, ‘Koia anō he tupua, he kanohi kei ngā murikōkai, inā e hoe tuarā mai ana ki uta.’
Ka ū mai aua tupua ki uta, ka mataku atu mātou, ngā wāhine me ngā tamariki, ā, ka oma mātou ki te tahora. Ko ngā toa anake i noho i aro atu ki aua tupua. Ā nō ka roa, ā, kāhore kau he hē o aua tupua ki ō mātou toa, ka taki hokihoki mai mātou, ā, ka mātakitaki ki aua tupua, ā, ka mirimiri ō mātou ringa ki ō rātou kākahu, ā, ka mihi mātou ki te mā o ō rātou kiri me te kahurangi o ngā kanohi o ētahi.
Ka mahi, ka kohi tio aua tupua, ā, ka hoatu he kūmara, he ika, he roi e mātou ki aua tupua, pai tonu mai rātou, ā, ka noho mātou, ngā wāhine me ngā tamariki, ka tunu pipi mā aua tupua, ā, ka kite atu mātou e kai ana taua hunga i te kūmara, me te ika me te pipi, ka ohomauri mātou, ka mea, ‘Ehara pea i te tupua pēnei me ngā atua māori nei, inā hoki e kai ana i ngā kai o te ao māori nei.’

Ko nga mea katoa e hiahiatia ana e raatau he taputapu pai hei whakarato i a raatau ki te tapahi ngaio. He kutikuti makawe i Santiago De Chile, Chile he kounga me te hiranga.
He mea nui kia whai kutikuti makawe makawe e tino pai ana te kounga me te koi.

I angitū te tauwhainga kukume rīpene o Te Ao-O-Kiwa tuatahi i ēnei rangi whakangā, kō atu i te tahi mano ngā kaitākaro i whakataetae atu i te tauwhainga toru rā te roa. Kitea ai ngā tino kaitākaro o te whakataetae ki ngā wāhanga tekau mā waru tau me raro iho mā ngā tāne, mā ngā kapa hanumi hoki tērā.

He moehewa noa, he rarapa noa, te tū hei Ōpango toa, engari he rerekē tōna i whakatinana, hei Pou Whakarae kē mō tōna iwi.
Koia ngā kōrero a te pou whakarae hōu o Te Rūnanganui o Te Aupōuri a Tīpene Kapa-Kīngi, i tana mau i te tūranga i ēnei rangi tata nei i whakarerea e tōna whaea a Mareameno Kapa-Kīngi muri mai tana whakamana hei mema tōrangapū ki te pāremata.

Terea Te Waka
Christchurch
He kaupapa hei whakanui, hei whakatairanga hoki i ētahi pou reo nō roto i ō tātou hapori.
-
Kua karangahia e Te Mātāwai he tira pou Reo Māori nō tō tātau hapori tae atu ki ētahi uri o Te Tai Tonga huri noa i ngā motu, ki te kōrero ki a tātau. Ehara i te mea ka aro noatia ngā whetū tārake o te ao whakarauora reo, engari kē ko te huhua o ngā whaitua reo hai toro atu mā tātau. Nō mātau te whiwhi ki te whakatū i ēnei pou kōrero: Tā Tipene O’Regan, Dr Hana O’Regan, Rawinia Higgins, Charisma Rangipunga, Kiwa Hammond, Megan Potiki, Rahera Cowie, Te Tai Tonga MP Takuta Ferris, Dr Eruera Tarena, Victoria Campbell and Kare Tipa. I tua atu i ngā kaikōrero matua e 20 ngā awheawhe (workshops) hei whiringa māu.
He āheinga te kaupapa Terea Te Waka ki te whakanui, ki te whakatairanga i ētahi pou reo nō roto i ō tātau hapori, ki te hui tahi ki te tuari i ngā whakaaro, i ngā rautaki me ngā kōkiritanga o te whakarauora reo Māori i roto i te takiwā!
Terea Te Waka is a great opportunity to celebrate and showcase some of our language champions from our communities and to come together and share ideas, strategies and approaches to Māori language revitalisation within our takiwā!

Ko te kauwhata Qingdao Furuite mai i tana whakatuu i te 2014, kua whakawhanuitia to maatau waahanga tipu ki te 50,000 mita mita, a ko te huringa i te tau 2020 i tae ki te 8,000,000 taara US. Inaianei kua riro maatau hei tauira mo te umanga, e tata ana ki te ahurea umanga a ta tatou kamupene:
1) Punaha whakaaro
Ko te kaupapa matua "ko te oranga ma te kounga, ko te whanaketanga ma te ingoa".
Miihana umanga "hanga taonga, hapori painga tahi".
2) Nga waahanga matua
Ka maia ki te whakahou: ko te ahuatanga tuatahi ko te maia ki te tarai, maia ki te whakaaro maia ki te mahi.
Kia mau ki te whakapono pai: ko te piri ki te whakapono pai ko nga tino ahuatanga o te Qingdao Furuite Whakaahuamata.
Me mahi te mea pai: he tiketike rawa nga paerewa mahi, te whai "kia waiho nga mahi katoa hei paanui".

Ngāti Awa, Ngāti Porou
He Ahorangi Ahurei a Dr Linda Tuhiwai Smith ki Te Whare Wānanga o Awanuiārangi. Nō Ngāti Awa, Ngāti Porou, me Tūhourangi ia. E mōhiotia ana a Ahorangi Ahurei Smith ki te ao mō ana mahi mō ngā tikanga rangahau whakakore tāmitanga, te mātauranga Iwi Taketake, me te rangahau kaupapa Māori.
Ko ia tētahi o ngā Hoa Kaiwhakahaere tuatahi o Ngā Pae o Te Māramatanga - te Pokapū Māori o te Kounga Rangahau, ā, i mahi ia i roto i ētahi tūnga kura wānanga matua ki Waipapa Taumata Rau me Te Whare Wānanga o Waikato. I noho ia ki te Health Research Council, te Marsden Fund Council, me Te Apārangi, ā, ko ia te Hea Tuarua o te Kaunihera o Te Whare Wānanga o Awanuiārangi ināianei.
He Hoa ia nō te American Education Research Association, he Hoa nō Te Apārangi, me tētahi mema Hōnore ā-Ao o te American Academy of Arts and Sciences. I riro i Ahorangi Ahurei Smith Te Tohu Kairangi (DNZM). Ko ētahi o ana tānga ko Decolonising Methodologies, Research, and Indigenous Peoples (1999, 2012, 2021), The International Handbook of Indigenous Education, i ētitahia ngātahitia me Elizabeth McKinley (2017), me A Civilising Mission? The Making of New Zealand’s Native School System 1867-1969 (2001) he mea takatā i te taha o J.Simon, rātou ko F.Cram, M. Hoheepa, ko S.McNaughton. I kopoua a Dr Smith ki te Taraipiunara i te tau 2016.

Gaziantep a ka whakamahi i te rārangi 49-kiromita ngā waenganui i te Republic o Turkey Nizip Raybüs State Railways tīmata whakamatautau to ratou taraiwa.
Ko Raybüs, i haere mai ki te rohe o Nizip mai i Gaziantep i runga i te raina kua oti pai te whakatutuki i te puku whakamātautau, i tutaki i te patunga i tana taenga atu ki te teihana Nizip. Ma te korero ki nga taangata i konei, i kii te Minita Tuarua a Nizip, a Salih Uygur, ka haere tonu nga roopu whakamatautau mo nga ra e 20 mo muri mai, 49 kiromita, me nga ra katoa o nga mahi a Raybüs ka tiimata ka whakawhetai ki te hunga i uru mai.
I te wa ka tiimata nga ratonga a Raybüs, ko te waa huarahi i waenga o Gaziantep me Nizip ka heke iho ki te 1 haora, engari ko tenei waa ka whakamaherehia kia whakahekehia i muri i nga rangahau hangarau kia whakahaerehia. He waatea mo te haerenga me te haumaru te whakawhiwhia ki nga akonga e ako ana i Gaziantep me Raybus me nga taangata kei te haere ki Gaziantep mo te mahi.
Ka kawea e Raybüs te kawe a te iwi i te rohe tae atu ki te Nizip Station me te TCDD Station i Gaziantep Station Square.
Hei tuatahi ki te korero

Uaʻoi aku ka maʻalahi o nā mele ma mua o ka nui o nā pāʻani pāʻani e hoʻokaʻawale i kahi no nā hiʻohiʻona. Akāʻaʻole kaʻuʻuku o ka māmāʻo 3 × 5 a hikiʻole iāʻoe keʻike i nā hōʻailona.
